opy\"\n+      ],\n+      \"reversibility\": \"easy\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"d3\",\n+      \"decision\": \"Emit server-side `<title>`, `<meta name=\\\"description\\\">`, and Open Graph `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:type`, and `og:url` tags for SPA HTML responses, and skip `twitter:*` and `og:image` for this task.\",\n+      \"based_on\": [\"q3\", \"q5\"],\n+      \"alternatives_rejected\": [\n+        \"Emit only JSON metadata without HTML head injection\",\n+        \"Expand scope to Twitter tags and preview images now\"\n+      ],\n+      \"reversibility\": \"easy\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"d4\",\n+      \"decision\": \"Resolve absolute preview URLs from a new `BAYES_PUBLIC_ORIGIN` config when present, otherwise fall back to request host/proto headers with a localhost default for non-requested code paths.\",\n+      \"based_on\": [\"q4\"],\n+      \"alternatives_rejected\": [\n+        \"Hard-code a single production origin in source\",\n+        \"Depend only on request headers with no explicit config override\"\n+      ],\n+      \"reversibility\": \"medium\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"d5\",\n+      \"decision\": \"Preserve the existing SPA fallback for `/markets/{id}` and serve generic metadata when the requested market does not exist instead of returning an HTML 404.\",\n+      \"based_on\": [\"q6\"],\n+      \"alternatives_rejected\": [\n+        \"Return a true HTML 404 for missing market deep links\"\n+      ],\n+      \"reversibility\": \"medium\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"steps\": [\n+    {\n+      \"step\": 1,\n+      \"task\": \"Add backend helpers for canonical public-origin resolution, normalized market preview payloads, and HTML head tag injection for SPA shell responses.\",\n+      \"depends_on\": []\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"step\": 2,\n+      \"task\": \"Register `GET /v1/markets/{id}/meta`, include it in the service index, and wire the request-aware origin into API and static HTML paths.\",\n+      \"depends_on\": [1]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"step\": 3,\n+      \"task\": \"Expose the new preview contract in frontend API types/client and add request-level tests for the new route and HTML metadata behavior.\",\n+      \"depends_on\": [1, 2]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"step\": 4,\n+      \"task\": \"Update the frontend HTML template defaults if needed, rebuild committed dist assets, run targeted backend/frontend tests, and commit the final patch.\",\n+      \"depends_on\": [3]\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"spawn_children\": false,\n+  \"children\": []\n+}\ndiff --git a/.fleet/tasks/bayes-market-0e6/questions.json b/.fleet/tasks/bayes-market-0e6/questions.json\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 00000000..4891cbb2\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/.fleet/tasks/bayes-market-0e6/questions.json\n@@ -0,0 +1,75 @@\n+{\n+  \"phase\": \"question\",\n+  \"questions\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q1\",\n+      \"question\": \"What exact JSON contract should `GET /v1/markets/{id}/meta` expose: a normalized preview object (for example `title`, `description`, `url`, `image`, `siteName`) or a raw map of HTML meta-tag names to values?\",\n+      \"category\": \"requirements\",\n+      \"why_it_matters\": \"The endpoint does not exist yet, and the task only names the route. The response shape determines the backend handler, frontend types/client surface, and the test contract.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q2\",\n+      \"question\": \"What should the share-preview copy actually contain for a market: just the stored `title` and `description`, or should it include live state such as status, top probabilities, resolution, or expiry in the generated description/title?\",\n+      \"category\": \"design\",\n+      \"why_it_matters\": \"The current market model already has several candidate fields for preview text. Without a canonical rule, the OG tags and `/v1/markets/{id}/meta` payload could drift or produce weak previews.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q3\",\n+      \"question\": \"Which meta tags are required for `/markets/{id}` HTML: only core Open Graph tags (`og:title`, `og:description`, `og:type`, `og:url`), or also `twitter:*`, standard `<meta name=\\\"description\\\">`, and `og:image`?\",\n+      \"category\": \"requirements\",\n+      \"why_it_matters\": \"There is no existing head-management layer in the frontend, so the implementation and test matrix depend on the minimum tag set that must be emitted server-side.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q4\",\n+      \"question\": \"How should absolute URLs be derived for preview metadata, especially `og:url` and any image URL: from the incoming request host/proto headers, from a fixed public origin such as `https://bayes.futarchy.ai`, or by some new config value?\",\n+      \"category\": \"design\",\n+      \"why_it_matters\": \"Link-preview crawlers generally need absolute URLs, but the codebase does not currently expose a canonical public-origin configuration for market pages.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q5\",\n+      \"question\": \"Is an `og:image` required for this task, and if so, what asset or generation strategy should be used given that the repo currently has no checked-in image assets for Bayes Market?\",\n+      \"category\": \"requirements\",\n+      \"why_it_matters\": \"An image materially affects link previews, but there is no existing logo/card asset or image-generation path in the repo. That choice changes both implementation scope and test expectations.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q6\",\n+      \"question\": \"What should a direct request to `/markets/{id}` do when the market id does not exist: continue serving the SPA shell with generic metadata so the client shows its current error state, or return a true HTTP 404 HTML/JSON response?\",\n+      \"category\": \"requirements\",\n+      \"why_it_matters\": \"The backend currently falls back to `frontend/dist/index.html` for suffixless routes, so missing-market deep links already return the SPA shell. Changing that behavior affects UX