st for comments\"\n+      ],\n+      \"reversibility\": \"medium\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"d2\",\n+      \"decision\": \"Use a plain-text comment schema of {commentId, marketId, seq, accountId, body, createdAt}; accept POST bodies shaped as {accountId, body, idempotencyKey?}; trim whitespace, reject blank bodies, and cap body length at 2000 characters.\",\n+      \"based_on\": [\"q2\", \"q4\", \"q6\"],\n+      \"alternatives_rejected\": [\n+        \"Introducing a separate author/display-name model\",\n+        \"Supporting Markdown or rich text formatting\",\n+        \"Adding updatedAt before edit support exists\"\n+      ],\n+      \"reversibility\": \"easy\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"d3\",\n+      \"decision\": \"Make comment POSTs inherit the existing protected-write flow and rate limiting through the trade_write category, allow reads for all market statuses, and allow posting only while a market is active.\",\n+      \"based_on\": [\"q3\", \"q7\"],\n+      \"alternatives_rejected\": [\n+        \"Bypassing X-Bayes-Agent-Id validation and rate limiting for comments\",\n+        \"Allowing posting on resolved, closed, or draft markets\"\n+      ],\n+      \"reversibility\": \"easy\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"d4\",\n+      \"decision\": \"Mirror the market event pagination contract for comments with ascending seq order and {fromSeq, limit, returned, nextFromSeq}, and render the discussion thread directly on the market detail page with a session-gated composer.\",\n+      \"based_on\": [\"q5\", \"q10\"],\n+      \"alternatives_rejected\": [\n+        \"A reverse-chronological comments API\",\n+        \"Hiding the entire discussion section when no accountId is configured\"\n+      ],\n+      \"reversibility\": \"easy\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"steps\": [\n+    {\n+      \"step\": 1,\n+      \"task\": \"Add backend comment storage, ids/sequences, request validation, GET/POST handlers, service index updates, and protected-write category cove